<center><big><big><big>DISCOVERY LOG.1</big></big></big></center>
<div style="background-color:#e5e4e2; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px dotted #000000; border-radius: 3px">
The following log details 27 year old Martin Moore entering Level 93 and documenting the effects of the Age-Altering Anomaly. During his exploration, Martin also encounters Walter, his family dog.
----
'''Date:''' 7/8/2002<br>
'''Location(s):''' Level 93<br>
'''People:''' Martin Moore<br>
'''Uploaded by:''' Unknown
----
'''<START OF LOG>'''

00:00

Martin enters Level 93 through an unknown way.

00:02

Martin: "This is a bit weird... Just an old house."

Martin: "Kinda looks like my mom's house for some reason."

Martin looks around the living room before walking into the kitchen.

00:04

Martin checks several kitchen cabinets and opens the refrigerator.

Martin: "Everything actually works..."

Martin picks up a landline phone and dials a random number.

Only static can be heard.

Martin: "...Yeah, that's not creepy."

00:06

Martin enters a bathroom and looks into the mirror.

Martin: "...What?"

Martin steps closer to the mirror.

Martin: "I look... younger."

00:09

Martin no longer has a beard and estimates his age to be around 18 years old.

Martin: "Uhhh... I'm so confused..."

Martin continues staring into the mirror before touching his face several times.

Martin: "This doesn't make any sense."

00:13

Martin continues exploring the house.

Martin: "It's way too quiet in here."

00:18

Martin enters the living room and notices his dog, Walter, lying on the floor.

Martin: "...Walter?"

Walter immediately stands up and walks over to Martin, wagging his tail.

Martin: "No way..."

Martin kneels down and pets Walter for around three minutes.

00:21

Martin: "You're coming with me this time."

Martin continues exploring the house with Walter following him. The dog behaves normally.

00:26

Martin discovers an exit from Level 93 and attempts to leave while calling Walter to follow him.

Martin: "Come on, Walter!"

As Martin exits the level, Walter stops just before the doorway. Martin turns around and watches Walter disappear without any visible movement or sound.

00:27

Upon returning to a safe level, Martin knows that Walter did not exit with him. Martin's appearance immediately returns to normal.

Martin: "...I guess you were never really here."

'''<END OF LOG>'''
----
This log provided the first documented evidence that pets encountered within Level 93 are unable to leave the level.
